# Cloudflare Pages SPA fallback.
#
# Deliberately NOT a blanket `/* / 200` — on this deployment that
# wildcard intercepted /assets/*.js and /assets/*.css too (verified:
# the hashed bundle requests returned the SPA shell's text/html
# instead of the real file, even though the files were confirmed
# present in the upload manifest and the rule itself was confirmed
# registered by Cloudflare). Enumerating every real app route instead
# means /assets/* and other real static paths never touch a
# _redirects rule at all and fall straight through to normal static
# serving. Keep this list in sync with src/router.tsx.
/palmier-suite    / 200
/motion-sheet     / 200
/canvas-creative  / 200
/studio           / 200
/issues           / 200
/issues/*         / 200
/archive          / 200
/launch/*         / 200
/refusals         / 200
/pressroom        / 200
/atelier          / 200
/about            / 200
/figma            / 200
/prototype        / 200
/privacy          / 200
/terms            / 200
